India Sensex Drops to Three-Month Low; DLF Sinks as Profit Falls

-- B y   R a j h k u m a r   K   S h a a w
-- 
2011-05-25T10:07:58Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-25/india-sensex-drops-to-three-month-low-dlf-sinks-as-profit-falls.html
India ’s benchmark stock index fell to
the lowest level in three months after the government’s chief
economic adviser said the country may miss its budget deficit
target and as the biggest developer’s profit missed estimates.  DLF Ltd. (DLFU) , India’s largest developer, plunged to a two-year
low after saying fourth-quarter earnings dropped 19 percent on
higher land and construction costs.  Infosys Technologies Ltd. (INFO) ,
the second-largest software exporter, retreated after saying it
received a subpoena from a U.S. court in  Texas  seeking documents
related to the company’s use of B1 business visas.  The Bombay Stock Exchange Sensitive Index lost 173.42, or 1
percent, to 17,838.55, according to preliminary closing prices
at 3:30 p.m. in Mumbai, heading for its lowest close since Feb.
28. The S&P CNX Nifty Index on the National Stock Exchange of
India Ltd. slid 0.8 percent to 5,349.40 and its May futures
settled at 5,348. The BSE 200 Index fell 0.7 percent.  To contact the editors responsible for this story:
Darren Boey at 
 dboey@bloomberg.net  